{"event_counts": {"item.completed": 11, "item.started": 5, "thread.started": 1, "turn.completed": 1, "turn.started": 1}, "last_agent_message": "Updated [memo.py](/var/folders/gc/8tw_jq1j09x5gsqhs1bc24cr0000gn/T/codex_benchmark_concurrency_safe_memoization_2086_8twatsri/concurrency_safe_memoization_2086/memo.py) to make memoization contention key-scoped. The decorator now uses a per-key in-flight record so only one thread computes a given key, concurrent callers for that same key wait on the shared computation, and successful results alone are cached. Failures are propagated to current waiters but are not stored in the cache, so later calls retry normally.

